==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clift
<hw>Clift</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st <er>Cliff</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A cliff.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That gainst the craggy <qex>clifts</qex> did loudly roar.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clift</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clift
<hw>Clift</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Cleft</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cleft of crack; a narrow
opening.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fork of the legs; the crotch.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clifted</ent>⟦br⟧
